node.text: Videos showing people smuggling migrants past Border Patrol checkpoints and flashing thousands of dollars in cash are being posted on TikTok, Texas State Troopers say. This is a new and dangerous tactic to recruit teens to drive migrants from the US-Mexico border to Houston and other Texas cities — with one video offering $4,500 per person they smuggle. CNN's @rosaflorescnn reports.

node.text: Anger over a controversial tax hike has turned into weeks of protests against police violence in Colombia. More than 42 people have been killed and hundreds have been injured. CNN’s Stefano Pozzebon reports from Bogota, Colombia.

node.title: ‘They have nothing to lose’: Protesters storm streets of Colombia

node.text:
Former President Barack Obama has joined NBA Africa as a strategic partner, the National Basketball Association announced on Tuesday. Obama "will help advance the league's social responsibility efforts across the continent, including programs and partnerships that support greater gender equality and economic inclusion," according to the NBA. He will also be a minority stakeholder in NBA Africa. Tap the link in our bio to learn more.⁠
⁠
(📸: Mark Wilson/Getty Images)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on July 31, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Hobby Lobby ordered to forfeit ancient artifact bought for $1.6 million in 2014'.

node.text:
A New York federal court has ordered US craft store Hobby Lobby to forfeit an ancient artifact purchased at a 2014 auction that "originated in the area of modern-day Iraq and entered the United States contrary to federal law," the Justice Department announced Tuesday. The artifact — known as the Gilgamesh Dream Tablet — is inscribed with a portion of "Gilgamesh," an epic poem considered one of the world's oldest works of literature. In 2014, Hobby Lobby, a privately owned arts and crafts retailer whose president is also the chairman of the Museum of the Bible in Washington, DC, bought the clay tablet for display in the museum from an international auction house for $1,674,000. Tap the link in our bio to learn more. ⁠
⁠
(📸: The Department of Justice)⁠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on July 31, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'French woman swapped diamonds for pebbles in elaborate $5.8 million heist CNN Exhibit VMH/2'.

node.text:
A 60-year-old French woman who posed as a diamond expert and entered a luxury London jeweler to steal seven precious gems in an elaborate daylight heist has been jailed for five and a half years, police said. Lulu Lakatos, who was part of an internationally organized crime gang, visited the Boodles store in London in March 2016 and played the role of a gemologist sent to inspect seven diamonds worth $5.8 million on behalf of a wealthy Russian investor. But Lakatos, who pretended she couldn't speak English in order to buy herself time in the store, placed a bag filled with the diamonds into her handbag and replaced it with another bag filled with pebbles. Tap the link in our bio to learn more. ⁠
⁠
(📸: Metropolitan Police)

node.text:
Make sure to look at Saturn this weekend for a once-a-year nighttime spectacle. Saturn will be at opposition — this is when Earth is between Saturn and the sun, so Saturn will be at its most luminous. Farmer's Almanac says you'll need a telescope to see those famous rings.⁠
⁠
(📸: NASA/HO/AFP/Getty Images)

node.text:
Swimmer Tom Dean was infected with Covid-19 twice before winning double gold in Tokyo Olympics.

CNN's @willripleycnn asked him what it was like getting ill before the Games. "It's an athlete's worst nightmare, especially during an Olympic year, so I'm glad I was able to come back from it," said Dean. "It was kind of a perfect storm of awful things because I couldn't train, I couldn't leave my flat and I was really ill."

Photo by CNN on July 30, 2021. May be an image of 3 people and text that says 'Japan has already won more gold medals this Olympics than the country has ever won before'.

node.text:
Japan secured a record-breaking 17th gold medal of the Tokyo Games on Friday, surpassing the country’s previous tally of 16 gold medals at Tokyo 1964 and Athens 2004. The 17th gold came in the men’s team épée – Japan’s first-ever gold medal in fencing.⁠
⁠
(📸: Andrew Medichini/AP)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on July 30, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and text that says 'Melinda French Gates and MacKenzie Scott have teamed up to give $40 million to support women CNN'.

node.text:
In a powerful philanthropic pairing, Melinda French Gates and MacKenzie Scott have teamed up to direct $40 million to advancing the power and influence of American women over the next decade. The donation is being awarded to winners of the Equality Can't Wait Challenge.⁠
⁠
Correction: A previous version of this post misspelled MacKenzie Scott's name.⁠
⁠
(📸: Ludovic Marin/Dia Dipasupil/AFP/Getty Images)⁠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on July 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'On Tuesday, enough Greenland ice melted to cover Florida in 2 inches of water CNN'.

node.text:
Follow ➡️ @cnnclimate ➡️ Greenland is experiencing its most significant melting event of the year as temperatures in the Arctic surge. Greenland lost more than 8.5 billion tons of surface mass on Tuesday, and 18.4 billion tons since Sunday, according to the Denmark Meteorological Institute. That would be enough to cover the entire state of Florida in two inches of water. While this week's total ice loss is not as extreme as a similar event in 2019 — a record melt year — the area of the ice sheet that's melting is larger. Tap the link in our bio to learn more.⁠
⁠
(📸: Delphotos/Alamy)⁠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on July 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Delta variant appears to spread as easily as chickenpox and cause more severe infection, internal CDC document says CNN'.

node.text: The Delta coronavirus variant surging across the United States appears to cause more severe illness and spread as easily as chickenpox, according to an internal document from the US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention. The document outlines unpublished data that shows fully vaccinated people might spread the Delta variant at the same rate as unvaccinated people. CDC Director Dr. Rochelle Walensky confirmed the authenticity of the document, which was first reported by The Washington Post. Tap the link in our bio to learn more.
